reason: To estimate the building's height, I need to see its full vertical structure; rotating the camera upward will reveal the roofline while maintaining the current heading toward the building.
I need to reorient toward the building by rotating right to face east (75° heading) while maintaining the upward pitch to view the building's full height.
To capture the building's full vertical extent, I need to tilt the camera upward while maintaining the eastward heading to see the roofline.

I need to rotate 75° right from north to face the building at 75°E while maintaining the upward pitch to observe its full vertical profile for height estimation.
I must tilt the camera upward while maintaining the 75°E heading to capture the building's full vertical profile from ground to roof for accurate height estimation.
